Una tarde Guayanesa es con MASA ! Una tarde en #Guayana es un cachito con café con leche cremoso, una tarde en Guayana es un pan dulce de coco, una cagalera ( Pan de Madama del Callao ) Entre nuestras masa tenemos el Domplin, las rebanadas, las rosquillas glaseadas, pan de bodega y un sin fin de “ masas “. Y por supuesto con los quesos frescos de la vía Upata como; Queso Guayanés, queso telita recién hecho y calientico, nata, y los quesos  duro… Y qué mejor manera de recordar a Guayana con un cachito caliente con café con leche y canela. 🫶🏼 #guayanes siempre y Guayanés orgulloso de Guayana 🤭🤗🙌🏼💯

Join us on a sweet journey with The Chocolate Pilots program! 🍫✈️ Born from a dream of sharing the joy of authentic Latin American chocolate, this gastronomic initiative brings together top pastry chefs in the U.S. @chef.gonzo  @luis_robledo_richards  @mitfher  @chef_jjohnmartin  @chefpastelero  as the driving force behind a purpose-driven venture.

Their mission: To craft not just incredible desserts and confections, but also to support and uplift communities in Latin America. Each creation is a piece of art, a whimsical delight that goes beyond taste – it’s about restoring happiness and creating positive memories.

Join us in spreading the joy, one delicious creation at a time on this first stop: New York City! 

 #chocolatepilots #republicadelcacao #joinlarepublicadelcacao

¡Acompáñanos en un increíble viaje con nuestros Chocolate Pilots! 🍫✈️ Esta iniciativa nace del sueño de compartir la alegría del chocolate latinoamericano más auténtico, este espacio gastronómico reúne a los grandes chefs pasteleros en EE. UU. como la fuerza detrás de esta empresa con propósito.

Únete a nosotros en este viaje y conoce nuestra primera parada: ¡Nueva York!

social_posts.post_text:
Meet our pilot @chefpastelero and embark on a flavorful journey with him, the Venezuelan Pastry Chef and Chocolatier, as he takes you through a remarkable culinary saga.
From his early roots winning dessert contests in Venezuela and earning the title of the state’s youngest Chef to representing his country in Guinness World Records, Víctor’s passion for the art of chocolate knows no bounds.
Venturing beyond borders, he honed his craft in Italy and Spain, training under renowned Chocolatier Luciano Pipolo. Back in Venezuela, Víctor crafted the largest chocolate coin, showcasing his dedication to the craft.
Now the Sous Chef at Love Makoto, he brings a fusion of global influences to the table, creating an exquisite symphony of flavors. Join Víctor on his international culinary exploration, where every creation tells a story of sweet victories and passion for the art.
Look at his creation here! #republicadelcacao #joinlarepublicadelcacao #chocolatepilots
.
.
Conoce a nuestro piloto @chefpastelero y embárcate en un viaje lleno de sabores con este gran Chef Pastelero y Chocolatier venezolano.

Desde sus inicios ganando concursos de postres en Venezuela y obteniendo el título de chef más joven del estado, hasta representar a su país en el Libro Guinness de los Récords, la pasión de Víctor por el arte del chocolate no conoce límites.

Explorando más allá de las fronteras, perfeccionó su técnica en Italia y España, formándose bajo la tutela del renombrado Chocolatier Luciano Pipolo. De vuelta en Venezuela, Víctor creó la moneda de chocolate más grande, mostrando su dedicación al arte. Actualmente, como Sous Chef en Love Makoto, fusiona influencias globales en cada plato, creando una exquisita sinfonía de sabores. Únete a Víctor en su exploración culinaria internacional, donde cada creación cuenta una historia de dulces victorias y pasión por el arte.
¡Descubre sus creaciones aquí!
#republicadelcacao #únetealarepublicadelcacao #chocolatepilots

Write a caption... Obsessed with freezing personal moments in time using my old Canon 450D, a nifty fifty, and a speedlite—because who needs a full frame when you've got passion and a hint of retro magic? 

📸✨ Lately, I've been chasing that elusive vintage vibe, and each click with my gear feels like a step back in time. Sorry, I can't help but have this overwhelming feeling of nostalgia.

🕰️ But let's take a pause from the snapshots and delve into another obsession of mine—the yearly tradition of baking the Venezuelan Torta Negra.

🍰 For the past few years, this culinary masterpiece has graced my Christmas table, thanks to the incredible Victor Millan, @chefpastelero , who generously shared the recipe with me. 

Inspired by memories of childhood and Venezuela's iconic Miramar chocolate candy, what was meant to be a quesillo-chocolate cake, a.k.a. the Impossible Cake, turned out to be Torta Negra.

🍫🍊 Collaborating with Victor, we added our own twist—an extra egg and a generous 2 cups of drunken fruit to the mix. 🍇🎄 

Every slice is a journey into tradition, love, and holiday magic. The consistency is so light, making it unbelievably ideal for any Nordic baking pan, and it doesn't stick. 

To finish it off and give it the real kick, once the cake is cooled, I soaked it with Diplomatic Rum Reserva exclusive and gave myself permission to garnish it with the best of the season, always adding a bit of magic with golden and edible shining pearls.

🔞Btw, this cake, unfortunately, is not suitable for kids, but you can always skip the part of the drunken fruits and the alcohol.

If you're craving a taste of nostalgia, leave me a comment, and I'll happily share the recipe with you! 🎅🏻✨ 

#VintageVibes #TortaNegraTradition #PassionOverPixels #yessicaduque #howidiplo #venezuelanfood #tortanegra #foodphotographer #foodstylingandphotography
